    //- High-impact, low-lift UX improvements
    section.container-wrapper.margin-top48.border-top
      .container-fluid
        .row.row-no-gutters.padding-top30
          .col-md-offset-1.col-md-10.col-sm-12
            h3 High-impact, low-lift UX improvements
        .row.row-no-gutters.padding-top30
          .col-md-offset-1.col-md-5.col-sm-12
            p Seeping through survey feedback, we notice that many backers, especially experienced backers, were confused as to where during checkout add-ons would be presented. I designed these “add-on available” pills as a quick fix to this issue.
          .col-md-5.col-sm-12 
            p.padding-top18 Although we might eventually want to incorporate add-ons into the project page, we want to see if this easy fix reduces the number of immediate concerns first.
        .row.row-no-gutters.padding-top30
          .col-md-offset-2.col-md-8.col-sm-12
            img(src="assets/img/kickstarter/add-on-pill.png").full
        .row.row-no-gutters.padding-top30
          .col-md-offset-1.col-md-5.col-sm-12
            p Another high-impact, low-lift UX improvement was the tab redesign. We noticed that creators were having trouble discovering the new add-on tab due to low interactivity.I originally repurposed an old Kickstarter tab pattern, but since it proved to hinder discoverability, I decided to redesign the entire tab navigation area on this page.
          .col-md-5.col-sm-12
            p Below, you can see the new tab design with icons for callout and clarification.
        .row.row-no-gutters.padding-top30
